Mobirix Co., Ltd. Privacy Policy
Mobirix Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as the “Company”) guides users through the procedures and standards for handling personal information in accordance with Article 30 of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」 so that users can safely use the homepage and mobile game service, and promptly resolves related grievances. We establish and disclose the following personal information processing policy in order to process it smoothly.
This privacy policy may change due to changes in related laws and guidelines or changes in the company's internal policies.
Article 1 [Items of personal information collected and used]
① For user identification, personal information may be collected as follows.
- [Required] Member information: external platform ID (Google, Apple, Facebook), domestic and foreign information
② When using game and portal services, comply with relevant laws, protect accounts and items, prevent fraudulent users, and provide stable service
The following information can be automatically collected and generated for provision, etc.
- [Required] When installing and using the game: nickname, download history, service use record, access log (including IP address), Bad use record, game version, payment record, terminal information (model name, OS information, terminal language and country information), device identification value, location information, Advertisement ID
③ When using the customer center to ensure smooth service use, additional information will be collected as follows.
- [Required] Customer consultation and complaint handling service: email address, game name, game ID, nickname, UID
- [Optional] Customer consultation and complaint handling service: Information required to confirm and respond to inquiries, terminal information (operating system, OS version, device ID, terminal model name), Payment details
④ Upon user request, personal information is requested as follows in order to process a refund. Depending on your payment information
The information collected may differ, and separate consent is obtained when necessary. Additionally, if the user is a minor
When processing a refund, additional information may be requested to verify your identity and the relationship with your legal representative.
- [Required] Payment/refund related information: email address, game name, game ID, nickname
- [Optional] Information related to payment/refund: Documents proving real name and family relationship to confirm payment in case of cancellation of payment by a minor (copy of resident registration / certificate of family relationship), materials required to confirm name of payment method (certificate of confirmation of subscription by minor, SKT - User agreement registration details / KT - Membership ledger certificate / LG - Subscription confirmation), Payment method confirmation document (Card payment statement / Card name confirmation), Payment method confirmation document (Card payment statement / Card name confirmation) Terminal information ( Operating system, OS version, device ID, terminal model name)
⑤ If the user wants to participate in the company's events and marketing, the user's personal information can be collected and used.
However, in this case, separate consent is obtained from the user.
- [Optional] Consent to receive advertising information: e-mail address, mobile phone number
Article 2 [Method of collecting personal information]
① The company may collect users' personal information through the following methods.
User's response in the process of customer inquiry
Collection through network communication information or access history
Article 3 [Purpose of collection and use of personal information]
① The company may use the collected personal information for the following purposes.
User management
- Individual identification according to content provision, duplicate subscription check, bad user management, abnormal user detection and use restriction,
Contract implementation, dispute handling
Provision of services
- Handling complaints and providing other customer services, delivering notices, providing paid payment services and notifying payment details, games
Support my co-op play and community service
New service development and marketing/advertisement utilization
- New service, event information guide, service quality improvement and statistical information processing
Article 4 [Retention and use period of personal information]
① Collected personal information is retained and used while user qualification is maintained, and when user qualification is lost or
Even if user qualifications are maintained, if the purpose of use of the information is completely achieved, it will be destroyed without delay.
It's possible. However, for a certain period of time according to the ‘retention period’ notified to the user when consenting to the collection and use of personal information.
We retain user information for a period of time.
Purpose of retention: Purpose of resolving consumer complaints and disputes upon withdrawal from game service
Retention period: 30 days
Retained items: access records (access date and time, connection location information), bad use records, download records, external platform ID, terminal information
Purpose of Retention: Purpose of marketing information and information related to event progress, selection of winners
Retention period: Deleted immediately after announcement of winners
Possessed items: Nickname, UID
② Regulations of related laws, such as the Consumer Protection Act in Electronic Commerce (hereinafter referred to as the ‘Electronic Commerce Act’) and the Protection of Communications Secrets Act
If it is necessary to preserve it, the company keeps user information for a certain period set by the relevant laws and regulations.
In this case, the company uses the information it keeps only for the purpose of keeping it, and the retention period is as follows.
Records on display and advertisement: 6 months (Electronic Commerce Act)
Records on contract or subscription withdrawal: 5 years (Electronic Commerce Act)
Records on payment and supply of goods: 5 years (Electronic Commerce Act)
Records on consumer complaints or dispute handling: 3 years (Electronic Commerce Act)
Service use records such as access log and access IP information: 1 year (Communications Secrets Protection Act)
Article 5 [Personal information destruction procedure and method]
① When personal information becomes unnecessary, such as the elapse of the personal information retention period and the achievement of the purpose of processing, the company immediately
We will destroy that personal information.
Destruction procedure – The company destroys personal information after the retention period has elapsed in a way that cannot be reproduced.
※ However, even if the user deletes the mobile game app (hereinafter referred to as “App”), the company collects personal information.
Information is not immediately destroyed.
Destruction method - Personal information stored in the form of an electronic file is destroyed using a technical method that cannot reproduce the record.
Delete.
- Personal information printed on paper is shredded with a shredder and destroyed.
Article 6 [Provision of personal information to third parties]
① The company handles users' personal information only within the scope specified in “Article 3 [Purpose of collection and use of personal information]”.
In principle, the user's personal information is not provided to the outside. However, the following cases are exceptions.
When the user agrees in advance
Pursuant to special provisions of law, judgments and orders of courts, binding orders or investigations of administrative agencies;
If there is a request from an investigative agency in accordance with the procedures and methods set forth in the law for the purpose
② In accordance with 『Personal Information Handling and Protection Guidelines in Emergency Situations』 jointly announced by government-related ministries, disasters, infectious diseases, and emergencies
In the event of an emergency, such as an incident or accident that poses a risk to the life or body of a person, or an imminent loss of property, the information subject
Personal information may be provided to related organizations without the consent of For details, please click here* is. (Put a link to 『Personal information processing and protection rules in case of emergency』 here*)
