Article 8 [Rights of users and legal representatives and how to exercise them]
① The legal representative of the user and children under the age of 14 (hereinafter referred to as “children”) is the individual himself or herself at any time.
You may request to view, correct, or delete information.
② The user and the legal representative of the child may exercise the rights specified in Paragraph 1 through the company's representative phone number, e-mail, etc.
You can contact the Privacy Officer (help@mobirix.com). The company protects users and children
If a request for the exercise of rights is received by a legal representative, we will take necessary measures without delay.
③ Request for viewing and suspension of processing of personal information is made by the user pursuant to Article 35 Paragraph 4 and Article 37 Paragraph 2 of the 『Personal Information Protection Act』
Rights may be limited.
④ Requests for correction and deletion of personal information may be rejected if there are provisions under other laws and regulations.
can.
Article 9 [Matters concerning the installation, operation, and refusal of automatic personal information collection devices]
① The company does not use 'cookies' that store and retrieve user information from time to time.
② The company allows online customized advertising providers to collect behavioral information.
Online customized advertisement: Analyzes the user's online usage type and access record to determine the user's characteristics It is a marketing technique that provides a considered service.
Online customized advertising providers: Google, Facebook, AdMob, etc.
How to collect behavioral information: Automatically collected when a user visits the website or runs the app
Collected behavioral information items: the user's website visit history and app usage history, and the user's search history
5 How to Opt Out of Advertising Identifier Collection
: Users can choose whether or not to receive customized advertisements, and advertisement identifiers are collected through the following routes
You can voluntarily turn off terminal options to prevent this from happening.
- AOS (Android Operating System): Device Settings -> Google -> Ads
Or device settings -> privacy -> advertising
- iOS (Apple Operating System): Device Settings -> Privacy -> Apple Ads
※ The release path may differ depending on the OS version.
Article 10 [Measures to Ensure Safety of Personal Information]
① In processing the personal information of users, the company does not allow personal information to be lost, stolen, leaked, forged, altered or damaged.
To ensure safety, we take the following measures.
Administrative measures: Establishment and implementation of internal management plan, training of employees and personal information handlers
Technical measures: management of access rights such as personal information processing system, installation and renewal of company-wide PC and server security programs
Physical measures: computer room access control
Article 11 [Criteria for determining additional use or provision without the consent of the information subject]
① The company complies with Articles 15 (3) and 17 (4) of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」 and Article 14-2 (1) of the Enforcement Decree of the 「Personal Information Protection Act」
Personal information may be additionally used and provided without the consent of the information subject. Accordingly, the company
In order to use and provide additional information without the consent of the subject, the following items were considered.
Whether the purpose of using or providing additional personal information is related to the original purpose of collection
Whether there is predictability of additional use and provision in light of the circumstances in which personal information was collected or the processing practices
Whether
Whether the additional use and provision of personal information unreasonably infringes on the interests of the information subject
Whether necessary measures have been taken to ensure safety, such as pseudonymization or encryption
